TITLE: Testing Business Logic with Session Dependency in Dart
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to test business logic that depends on a Session object using the withServerpod helper. It shows how to set up a test environment, insert test data, and validate business logic behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/serverpod/serverpod_docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.2.0/06-concepts/19-testing/03-advanced-examples.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
withServerpod('Given decreasing product quantity when quantity is zero', (
  sessionBuilder,
  _,
) {
  var session = sessionBuilder.build();

  setUp(() async {
    await Product.db.insertRow(session, [
      Product(
        id: 123,
        name: 'Apple',
        quantity: 0,
      ),
    ]);
  });

  test('then should throw `InvalidOperationException`',
      () async {
    var future = ProductsBusinessLogic.updateQuantity(
      session,
      id: 123,
      decrease: 1,
    );

    await expectLater(future, throwsA(isA<InvalidOperationException>()));
  });
});
```

