TITLE: AuthKey Table Definition
DESCRIPTION: YAML definition for the AuthKey table that handles user authentication. This table was moved from Serverpod core to the serverpod_auth module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/serverpod/serverpod_docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.1.0/08-upgrading/03-upgrade-to-two.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
### Provides a method of access for a user to authenticate with the server.
class: AuthKey
table: serverpod_auth_key
fields:
  ### The id of the user to provide access to.
  userId: int

  ### The hashed version of the key.
  hash: String

  ### The key sent to the server to authenticate.
  key: String?, !persist

  ### The scopes this key provides access to.
  scopeNames: List<String>

  ### The method of signing in this key was generated through. This can be email
  ### or different social logins.
  method: String
indexes:
  serverpod_auth_key_userId_idx:
    fields: userId
```

