TITLE: Serverpod Authentication Key Table Definition YAML
DESCRIPTION: Details the structure of the 'serverpod_auth_key' table as a YAML configuration for user authentication. Fields include user id, hash, key, scopes, and signing method. This structure guides implementing custom token management.
SOURCE: https://github.com/serverpod/serverpod_docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.0.0/12-upgrading/01-upgrade-to-two.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
class: AuthKey
table: serverpod_auth_key
fields:
  userId: int
  hash: String
  key: String?, !persist
  scopeNames: List<String>
  method: String
indexes:
  serverpod_auth_key_userId_idx:
    fields: userId

```

